               <p>The prosecutor detected the prisoner, who was his <rs id="t17851214-83-deflabel387" type="occupation">shopman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17851214-83-defend763 t17851214-83-deflabel387"></join>, going out of the shop with one of his hats in his breeches, which he deposed to.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. It is my own hat, one I had to dress and clean, and I wanted to conceal it; I have a licence to deal in hats.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. I am sure it was my hat.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17851214-83-verdict388" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17851214-83-verdict388" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Court. Prisoner, your defence is a very great aggravation of your crime, for nothing can be more suspicious or improper, than for a journeyman to deal in the same commodity which his master does on his own account; therefore, under all the circumstances of this case, I think I should not do my duty if I was not to order you to be <rs id="t17851214-83-punish389" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17851214-83-punish389" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17851214-83-defend763 t17851214-83-punish389"></join>
               transported for seven years
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the second Middlesex Jury before Mr. RECORDER.</p>
